8. Added database entity: Tenant
	Why we added it

    In a multi-tenant SaaS system, almost every business object will eventually belong to a tenant.

    For example, later we may have:

    Tenant → Users
    Tenant → Roles
    Tenant → Projects
    Tenant → Subscriptions
    Tenant → Settings

     :- @Entity means: This Java class maps to a database table.
     :- @Id means: This field is the primary key.
     :- @GeneratedValue means: The database will automatically generate a unique value for this field when a new record is inserted.
     :- @PrePersist runs before the record is first saved.
     :- @PreUpdate runs before the record is updated.

