What we added:

	TenantUpdateRequest
	PUT /api/tenants/{id}
	Tenant update logic
	Duplicate slug protection during update
	Why we added it

	Tenant data must be editable, but the slug must remain unique because later it will help identify tenants through URLs, headers, or subdomains.

	What you need to remember

	This part protects us from duplicate slugs:

	tenantRepository.findBySlug(request.slug())
			.ifPresent(existingTenant -> {
				if (!existingTenant.getId().equals(id)) {
					throw new DuplicateResourceException("Tenant slug already exists: " + request.slug());
				}
			});

	It allows the same tenant to keep its own slug, but blocks another tenant from using it.

Update Tenant Status:

	TenantStatusUpdateRequest
	PATCH /api/tenants/{id}/status
	Tenant activation/deactivation/suspension logic
	Cleaner invalid JSON/enum error handling
	Why we added it

	In SaaS platforms, tenant accounts should usually be disabled or suspended, not deleted. This preserves historical data, billing records, audit logs, and user activity.

	What you need to remember

	Use:

	INACTIVE

	when a tenant is simply disabled.

	Use:

	SUSPENDED

	when the tenant is blocked due to billing, abuse, policy violation, or administrative action.

	Use:

	ACTIVE

	when the tenant is allowed to use the platform normally.


