User Role Management
What we added:

	UserRole
    UserStatus
    AppUser entity
    AppUserRepository

    Why we added it

    A SaaS user should belong to a specific tenant. That is why AppUser has this relationship:

		@ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
		@JoinColumn(name = "tenant_id", nullable = false)
		private Tenant tenant;

    This means:

    Many users can belong to one tenant.
    What you need to remember:    We are using AppUser, not User, because User often conflicts with Spring Security classes later.

    Also, this constraint:
		columnNames = {"tenant_id", "email"}
    means the same email cannot be repeated inside the same tenant.
    But later, the same email could theoretically exist in another tenant:

    Tenant A → admin@example.com
    Tenant B → admin@example.com

    That is a common SaaS design choice.

    Now run the app and check H2 Console:

    SELECT * FROM APP_USERS;

    The table should exist and be empty.

