User Creation In a Tenant:
	What we added:

    AppUserCreateRequest
    AppUserResponse
    AppUserService
    AppUserController
    POST /api/tenants/{tenantId}/users
    GET  /api/tenants/{tenantId}/users
    Why we added it

    This establishes the first parent-child SaaS relationship:

    Tenant → Users

    A user is now scoped under a tenant, which is the foundation for tenant isolation later.

    What you need to remember

    This URL design:

    /api/tenants/{tenantId}/users

    means:

    Manage users belonging to one specific tenant

    Also, we normalize emails before saving:

    request.email().trim().toLowerCase()

    This prevents duplicate-looking emails like:

    Admin@Acme.com
    admin@acme.com

